## Preamble (not legally binding)

This license is derived from the Functional Source License, Version 1.1,
published by Sentry (https://fsl.software). The core structure —
license grant, patent grant, redistribution clause, trademark clause,
and the 2-year Apache-2.0 future license — is preserved verbatim.

The single material deviation from the canonical FSL is in the
**Competing Use** definition: the standard FSL prohibits only
*hosted-or-embedded-service* redistribution. This license prohibits
redistribution of the Software in *any* form — hosted, on-premises,
bundled, rebranded, or otherwise — where the resulting product or
service competes substantially with Softprobe's own commercial
offerings.

This is an intentionally stronger non-compete clause. Internal,
research, and consulting use at any scale remains unrestricted. Every
release still auto-converts to Apache-2.0 two years after its
publication date, at which point no Competing Use restriction applies.

